Some will be hand crafted, others will be procedurally generated. üöß

No two trips into the Dreamverse aka The Waking Realms will be the same. Each journey will offer very real rewards, but at the hazard of equally real risk.

Some of the shards you‚Äôll discover are tiny. Especially in the Alpha Game - exploration will be limited by our desire to get a playable game asap ‚ö°

As we get deeper into our roadmap, expect fully realized dungeon spaces. These shards will be sprawling, explorable worlds.

We don‚Äôt expect you to crack this particular lobster knuckle on your own‚Ä¶

üî• It‚Äôll take the entire community to unravel the story. üî•

Well, you‚Äôve got to play the game to find out‚Ä¶ but I‚Äôll give you a spoiler free preview. üëÄüåä

You‚Äôll explore an ocean of shattered realities - each one a ‚Äúshard‚Äù of a different biome. They‚Äôll be plucked from myth, popular culture, and even Earth‚Äôs history.

You‚Äôve set out from hell into the shifting Dreamverse. It‚Äôs a melting pot of everything in our cultural memory - from the Epic of Gilgamesh to Pepe the Frog.

What unspeakable horrors await you?

But look, this is kind of a ‚Äúneed to know‚Äù type of situation. I‚Äôll spare you the fine print. The key point is this: reality is seriously FUBAR‚Äôd in our game world. 

Now YOU need to figure out why‚Ä¶ and clean up the fucking mess. üîÆ
To quote Dr. Peter Venkman: ‚ÄúHuman sacrifice! Dogs and cats living together! Mass hysteria!‚Äù Just a really bad week for anyone into silly shit like ‚Äúcausality.‚Äù https://t.co/uh5kakKuCe
